{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "RadiationFundamentals",
        "description": "Composed radiation-fundamentals system from Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Chapter 4 (Eqs. 4.1-4.11). A pure structural aggregation (no coupling equations) of seven independent components: PhotonEnergy (photon energy-frequency-wavelength relations, Eq. 4.1), BlackbodyRadiation (Planck's law, Eq. 4.2), WienDisplacement (peak emission wavelength, Eq. 4.3), StefanBoltzmann (total emissive power, Eq. 4.4), PlanetaryEnergyBalance (Earth's equilibrium temperature, Eqs. 4.5-4.7), ClimateSensitivity (temperature response to forcing, Eqs. 4.8-4.10), and TOARadiativeForcing (net top-of-atmosphere flux, Eq. 4.11). Each component is inlined as a named subsystem; variables are dot-namespaced (RadiationFundamentals.<subsystem>.<var>). Migrated from GasChem.jl@8c12c048 src/radiation_fundamentals.jl:367 (`RadiationFundamentals` @component).",
        "tags": [
            "gaschem",
            "radiation",
            "composed-system",
            "seinfeld-pandis",
            "blackbody",
            "energy-balance",
            "climate-sensitivity",
            "planck-law"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z",
